%% LangGraph Conditional Routing Architecture

%% The 6-Agent Swarm Logic:
%% - Triage Agent: Analyzes the raw Prometheus payload. Extracts the service name,
%%   determines severity, and makes a routing decision (Is this actionable, or
%%   transient noise?).
%% - Investigation Agent: Reads the Triage context. (In Phase 7, this will execute
%%   MCP tools to fetch K8s logs/metrics). Appends findings to state.
%% - Resolution Agent: Reads findings. Queries RAG runbooks to determine the correct
%%   fix.
%% - Execution Agent: Drafts the actual Terraform or Kubernetes YAML patch.
%% - Review Agent: Halts execution for Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) approval.
%% - Incident Report Agent: Generates the final post-mortem and closes the ticket.

stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> TriageNode: Alert Received
    
    state Triage_Decision <<choice>>
    TriageNode --> Triage_Decision: Assess Severity
    
    Triage_Decision --> InvestigationNode: Severity == Critical/Warning
    Triage_Decision --> ReportNode: Severity == False Positive (Noise)
    
    InvestigationNode --> InvestigationNode: Need More Context (Cyclic)
    InvestigationNode --> ResolutionNode: Logs Gathered / RCA
    
    ResolutionNode --> ExecutionNode: Fix Proposed
    
    ExecutionNode --> ReviewNode: PR Drafted
    
    ReviewNode --> ReportNode: Approved
    ReviewNode --> ExecutionNode: Rejected / Rewrite (Cyclic)
    
    ReportNode --> [*]: Incident Closed